Note: Test negating variables (not just literals)
Note: This tests -variable syntax where variable is already defined

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Note: Test negating a positive variable
    Let x be 5
    Let neg_x be -x
    If neg_x is not equal to -5:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Test negating a negative variable (double negative)
    Let y be -10
    Let neg_y be -y
    If neg_y is not equal to 10:
        Return 2
    End If

    Note: Test negating in expression
    Let a be 7
    Let result be -a plus 3
    If result is not equal to -4:
        Return 3
    End If

    Note: Test negating variable in assignment
    Let b be 15
    Set b to -b
    If b is not equal to -15:
        Return 4
    End If

    Return 0
End Process
